place.name: ATTLEBRIDGE
place.gazetteerText: ATTLEBRIDGE, a parish in St. Faith district, Norfolk; on the river Wensum, 9 miles NW of Norwich r. station. It has a post office under Norwich. Acres, 1,267. Real property, £1,374. Pop., 93 Houses, 19. The living is a vicarage annexed to the rectory of Alderford, in the diocese of Norwich. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
